{#-
Sovereign dossier page skeleton (Constitution III.13 / Amendment W).

Deliberately prose-free: this is a scaffold page, not narrative copy. Every
value interpolated here is a plain string already resolved by
babylon.projection.vault.render (never a raw Optional SovereignView field —
Jinja's StrictUndefined only fires on genuinely *absent* names, and a
present-but-None field renders the literal text "None" rather than raising,
so render.py precomputes statblock_rows/absent_fields and the template only
ever touches those, the three always-present identity fields, and
sovereign.claimed_county_fips — guarded by "is truthy", which is safe for
both None and an empty tuple, for the Claims wikilink roster).

Fenced directives only ({statblock}/{absence}), matching
babylon.tui.directives.BabylonFence dispatch (ADR099: paired containers
break the 8.2.8 markdown walker).
-#}
